        <body>
            <p rend="align(center)">DEDICATION</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">OF THE</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">Sephardim Synagogue,</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">HOUSE OF <placeName>ISRAEL</placeName>,</p>
            <p rend="align(center)"><placeName>Baltimore</placeName>, <date>September 16<hi
                        rend="sup">th</hi>. 1857</date>.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">PROGRAMME.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The bearers of the Law will form in the Vestry Room, and walk
                in<lb/> Procession to the door of the Synagogue, when the <persName>REV. SOLOMON
                    JACOBS</persName>,<lb/> of <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>, will knock at
                the door three times, and say:</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">“Open for me the gates of righteousness, that I may enter through
                them, to<lb/> praise the Lord.”</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The Minister inside answers:</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">“This is the gate of the Lord, into which the righteous shall
                enter.”</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The persons bearing the Law enter and ascend the Tebah, during
                which</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">THE CHOIR WILL SING A QUARTETTE,</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">FROM <persName>MENDELSSHON'S</persName> “ORATORIO OF
                    <persName>ELIJAH</persName>.”</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">After which the Congregation sing,</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Baruch haba beshem adonai.</p>
            <p><persName>REV. J. M. D. SOLLA</persName>, the Minister, then says:</p>
            <p>“Blessed art thou O Lord, our God, King of the Universe, who hast preserved<lb/> us
                alive, sustained us, and brought us to enjoy this season!”</p>
            <p>During which the PERPETUAL LAMP is lighted,—and the</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">ARK OPENED.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">THE CHOIR SING ODECHA.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">THE SEVEN-CIRCUITS.</p>
            <p>During which the Minister and Congregation alternately repeat the<lb/> following</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">PSALMS,</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">30<hi rend="sup">th</hi>. 100<hi rend="sup">th</hi>. 122d.
                    127<hi rend="sup">th</hi>.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">Yimloch, by Minister, and 29<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Psalm by
                Congregation.</p>
            <p>After which the LAW is deposited in the ARK,—the Minister says,<lb/> “SHUBA,”—when
                the doors of the Ark are closed.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">SERMON BY <persName>REV. ISAAC LEESER</persName>.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">CONSECRATION HYMN,</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">Composed expressly for the occasion by <persName>D. N. Carvalho,
                    Esq.</persName>, sung by the CHOIR.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">SERMON BY <persName>REV. SOLOMON JACOBS</persName>.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">SOLO.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">SYMPHONY,</p>
            <p>During which free will Offerings will be collected.</p>
            <p>MISHEBERACHS will then be made for those who desire it.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">EVENING SERVICE BY <persName>REV. MR. LEESER</persName>.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">YIGDAL BY CHOIR.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)"><persName>JOHN D. TOV</persName>, PRINTER.</p>
